{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Scrap six-year time limit for claims in Overseas Operations Act",
        "additional_details": "We feel it discriminates against those who served in overseas operations compared to those who served at home or in non-combat roles abroad. We believe that tragically, and ironically, it targets the very people who put themselves in harm\u2019s way to protect the rights of every other citizen. We feel that if it wasn\u2019t so serious and disrespectful, it would be laughable.\r\n\r\nWe are calling for Part 2 of this Act to be scrapped \u2014 not amended, not delayed \u2014 scrapped. We believe that justice must be equal for all, or it is not justice at all.",
        "background": "We feel this time limit unfairly discriminates against veterans who may need more time to come forward with claims \u2014 especially in cases involving PTSD, delayed diagnoses, or where evidence surfaces later. ",
